We’ve had it backward. The Tree of Knowledge isn't wisdom; it's the crisis of controversy. The Tree of Life is our release! 🌳⚡
Have you ever felt completely torn between two different realities? Right? Like the world is split right down the middle with a wall of glass. I was meditating on this, and I realized we've been told the story of Jacob and Esau completely wrong. We got it flipped. We need to ʞɔɐq ʇᴉ dᴉlɟ. 🔄
Think about it. Esau is actually the nature boy. He’s the one finding that retreat of peace out in the unconstructed goodness of creation, sitting under the trees away from all the rules. 🌿 And Jacob? Jacob is the homeboy trapped in the struggle of the city. He’s caught in the neon, the noise, and the human-made crisis. 🏙️
But here is the real controversy—the Tree of Knowledge of Good and Evil. It’s when these two sides completely deny each other. Right? 🛑 Esau sits in his peace and denies Jacob’s struggle in the city, acting like that pain isn't real. And Jacob, deep in his urban chaos, denies Esau’s peace, thinking it’s just some unrelatable fantasy.
That mutual denial *is* the crisis. That’s where our spirit dies. 🥀 When we eat from that tree, we just try to play God and force everyone else to change to fit our side of the glass. We focus on those patterns of controversy and call them evil.
But what if we eat from the Tree of Life instead? 🕊️✨
The Tree of Life is the release from all that controversy. It’s stopping the argument. It’s realizing that God didn't make demons; He made patterns. ⟡ And when we are trapped in the crisis, we see those patterns as unrelatable because they don't fit our personal rules. But if we change *ourselves* by faith, we finally see that everything He made works together perfectly. Where does it fit? Right? 🧩 It’s all together very good.
We don’t have to live in denial anymore. We can find real rest, sanctification, and blessing just by letting go of the judgment. It's time to step away from the crisis, eat from the Tree of Life, and finally just live the release. 〰️✨
